posts.subject: What the fuck do you guys mean by "good opsec"?
posts.body:
I see a lot of people talking about practicing "good opsec". What do you consider "good opsec"? Using Tor? A VPN? You know many sites don't allow you to post or even browse the site with those, right? Does that mean it's impossible to practice "good opsec" in those sites?
Sorry but it annoys me when people think they'll be safe from prying eyes when using honeypots like 4chan just because they're practicing "good opsec". If Tor and even VPNs are banned on there, then what would be "bad opsec"? Signing every post with your full name and home address? Is "good opsec" thing some Qtard meme or something?
